(1+x)^{n}=\sum_{k=0}^{n}\binom{n}{k}x^{k}
nx(1+x)^{n-1}=\sum_{k=0}^{n}\binom{n}{k}kx^{k}.
\sum_{k=0}^{n}\binom{n}{k}kx^{k}=\sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac{n!}{(k-1)!(n-k)!}x^{k}
=nx\sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac{(n-1)!}{(k-1)!(n-k)!}x^{k-1}=nx\sum_{k=0}^{n-1}\binom{n-1}{k}x^{k}=nx(1+x)^{n-1}.
